FCT justifies planned renovation There is disquiet over a plan by the federal government to spend N37bn in the renovation of a section of the National Assembly complex in Abuja to make the place “conducive” for lawmakers. The money was captured in the N10.594 trillion 2020 budget signed into law by President Muhammadu Buhari on…  N37 billion enough to build 10,360 classrooms N37bn can build 12,333 2-bedroom bungalows Gov. El-Rufai allocates N440m for women affairs